org.sbolstandard.core2

Class SBOLWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLWriter

  • public class SBOLWriter
extends Object
    Provides methods to output SBOL files in XML/RDF format.
    Version:
    2.1
    Author:
    Tramy Nguyen, Chris Myers, Matthew Pocock, Goksel Misirli

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static boolean keepGoing
      A true value of the keepGoing flag tells the SBOL writer to continue writing an output file, after it encounters an SBOL conversion exception; a false value forces the writer to stop writing after it encounters an SBOL conversion exception.

      • setKeepGoing

        public static void setKeepGoing(boolean keepGoing)
        Sets the value for the keepGoing flag to the given boolean value.

        A true value means that reading will keep going after encountering an SBOL validation exception, and a false value means otherwise.

        Parameters:
        keepGoing - the boolean value for the keepGoing flag

      • write

        public static void write(SBOLDocument doc,
                         String filename,
                         String fileType)
                  throws IOException,
                         SBOLConversionException
        Outputs this SBOL document's data from serialization in the given serialization format to a new file with the given file name.

        This method calls write(SBOLDocument, File, String) by passing this SBOL document, and a new file with the given file name and type.

        Parameters:
        doc - the given SBOLDocument object
        filename - the name of the serialized output file
        fileType - the given file format, such as RDF/XML, JSON, or Turtle.
        Throws:
        IOException - see IOException
        SBOLConversionException - - problem found during serialization
